es":"Enlisted upon high school graduation; stationed in Japan and Korea. Discharged Oct 1947 as corporal."},{"role":"NCO","organization":"South Dakota National Guard, SVC Co. 196th RCT","start_year":1947,"end_year":1970,"notes":"Recalled to federal service 1950 (Korean War) — Camp Carson Colorado Springs CO, Ft. Richardson Anchorage AK. Retired 1970 as Master Sergeant (M/Sgt) — 23 years total Guard service."},{"role":"DOT employee","organization":"South Dakota Department of Transportation","start_year":1953,"end_year":1990,"notes":"Worked 37 years for SD DOT, retiring 1990. Also volunteered as chief clerk and director of Pierre Legion Relays."}],"tags":["korean_war","south_dakota_migration","military","veteran"],"military_service":[{"war":"Korean War","war_id":"WAR014","rank_start":"Private","rank_end":"Master Sergeant (M/Sgt)","rank_year_start":1946,"rank_year_end":1970,"unit":"U.S. Army 21st Regt, 24th Inf Div (1946-1947); SD National Guard SVC Co. 196th RCT (1947-1970)","role":"Career soldier","service_years":"1946-1970 (24 years total)","notes":"Enlisted 1946 after Gettysburg High School graduation; stationed in Japan and Korea with 21st Regt, 24th Inf Div. Discharged Oct 1947 as corporal. Enlisted in SD National Guard same year. Recalled to federal service 1950 (Korean War) at Camp Carson CO and Ft. Richardson AK. Retired 1970 as M/Sgt (Master Sergeant)."}],"sources":[{"short":"Findagrave (Pierre obituary, via Sam)"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"military","header":"Korean War Army veteran, SD National Guard career","body":"Howard Ray Tousley enlisted in the U.S. Army upon graduating Gettysburg High School in 1946 and was stationed in Japan and Korea with the 21st Regiment of the 24th Infantry Division. He transferred to the South Dakota National Guard in 1947, was recalled to federal service in 1950 for the Korean War (stationed at Camp Carson CO and Ft. Richardson AK), and retired from the Gu